  "texts": [
    "Image detection represents an advanced computational technology that processes visual data to identify and locate specific objects within images.",
    "This methodology differs from image classification, which categorizes entire images without delineating object locations.",
    "Image detection focuses on recognizing the presence and spatial positioning of objects, often utilizing bounding boxes to indicate their locations within a given frame.",
    "The significance of image detection spans multiple domains due to its ability to automate and enhance processes that previously relied on human visual assessment.",
    "For instance, image detection improves operational efficiency in manufacturing quality control by enabling the rapid and accurate inspection of numerous components."
  ],
